# Affordances (Server-Driven Permissions)

## Three primitives — use the right one

| Primitive | When |
|---|---|
| `can(subject, Capability.X.Y)` | Object is in scope and its type extends `WithPermittedActions` |
| `useCan(Capability.X.Y)` | No object (page guard, create button, conditional prop) |
| `<Can capability={Capability.X.Y}>` | Declarative JSX wrapper (FABs, buttons) |

**Never** write inline ownership logic (`user.id === currentUserId`). The backend is the single source of truth.

## Object-level vs ambient

```tsx
// OBJECT-LEVEL — subject has permitted_actions
const canUpdate = can(experiment, Capability.Experiment.UPDATE);
{canUpdate && <EditButton />}

// AMBIENT — scope/role check, no object
const canRead = useCan(Capability.TestRun.READ);
if (!canRead) return <AccessDenied resource="test runs" />;

// DECLARATIVE ambient
<Can capability={Capability.TestSet.CREATE}>
  <Fab icon={<FabAddIcon />} />
</Can>
```

## Types that carry object-level affordances

`TestResult`, `ExperimentRead`, `Task`, `TestRun`, `Comment` — their interfaces extend `WithPermittedActions`.

Everything else (Behavior, Metric, Endpoint, TestSet, Source, …) → use `useCan` / `<Can>`.

## Page read guard

Every protected page must guard the READ capability:

```tsx
const canRead = useCan(Capability.Foo.READ);
if (!canRead) return <AccessDenied resource="foos" />;
```

## Adding affordances to a new resource

1. **Backend**: add `WithPermittedActions` to the Pydantic response schema.
2. **Frontend**: extend the TS interface with `WithPermittedActions` from `@/types/affordances`.
3. Use `can(subject, …)` instead of `useCan` for that resource.
4. Add any new capability strings to `apps/frontend/src/constants/capabilities.ts` (must mirror backend `Permission` enum).

## Jest mocks

Any test that renders a component using affordance primitives must mock the module:

```ts
jest.mock('@/components/common/Can', () => ({
  useCan: () => true,
  Can: ({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) => <>{children}</>,
  can: () => true,
}));
```

## Key files

- `src/components/common/Can.tsx` — primitives
- `src/contexts/PermissionsContext.tsx` — ambient scope provider
- `src/constants/capabilities.ts` — `Capability` enum
- `src/types/affordances.ts` — `WithPermittedActions` interface
- `apps/backend/.../schemas/affordances.py` — backend mixin
- `apps/backend/.../auth/capabilities.py` — `Permission` enum
